{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c92fb125-db9f-42e5-894d-ef9aa1b2be28","content":"Use **`dotnet run`**, not `dotnet test`.\n\nHot reload with `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HotReload` works through the **Microsoft Testing Platform** runner, which is invoked via `dotnet run`. The flow is:\n\n```bash\ndotnet run --project TestProject.csproj\n```\n\nThis starts the test process in a long-running mode that watches for file changes and re-runs affected tests automatically.\n\n`dotnet test` launches a separate test host process and exits — it doesn't support the hot-reload watch loop. Since your project already has `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` enabled and the HotReload package referenced, `dotnet run` is the correct command.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7e491472-8a69-4f9e-88f4-ec689d5f3936","outputTokens":160},"id":"9850f4e3-d189-4fae-bbcf-d6ee76a8a3bf","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:45:28.135Z","parentId":"2ebd60b1-70c9-40fb-b555-fb4925da64e4"}
